=== 早期历史 ===
目前没有任何确切的历史证明谁创立或命名了吉隆坡<ref name="sutanpuasa"/><ref name="gulllick 3">{{cite journal|url=http://myrepositori.pnm.gov.my/bitstream/123456789/4317/1/JB1869_GOKL.pdf|title=The Growth of Kuala Lumpur and the Malay Communities in Selangor Before 1880|author=J.M. Gullick|journal=Journal of the Malaysian Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society|volume=LXIII|date=June 1990|issue=1|pages=15–17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815212619/http://myrepositori.pnm.gov.my/bitstream/123456789/4317/1/JB1869_GOKL.pdf|archive-date=2016-08-15|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>Abdul Samad Ahmad, ''Pesaka Selangor'', Dewan Bahasa dan Pustaka, Kuala Lumpur, (1937 edisi Jawi), 1966.</ref><ref name="Fatt2011">{{cite book|author=Lam Seng Fatt|title=Insider's Kuala Lumpur (3rd Edn): Is No Ordinary Travel Guide. Open Your Eyes to the Soul of the City (Not Just the Twin Towers...)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rRCJAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA18|date=2011-03-15|publisher=Marshall Cavendish International Asia Pte Ltd|isbn=978-981-4435-39-0|pages=18–|access-date=2018-04-05|archive-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804130120/https://books.google.com/books?id=rRCJAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA18|url-status=live}}</ref>。吉隆坡最初是一个位于双溪鹅麦和双溪巴生（巴生河）的交汇处，只有几间房屋和商店的小村庄。吉隆坡大约在1857年成为一个[[城镇|城镇]]，当时[[巴生|巴生]]的马来酋长{{tsl|en|Raja Abdullag|拉惹阿都拉}}在他的兄弟{{tsl|ms|Raja Jumaat ibni Raja Jaafar|拉惹朱马安}}的帮助下聘请了来自{{tsl|en|Lukut|卢骨}}的[[马来西亚华人|华人]]矿工到[[巴生谷|巴生谷]]开采[[锡|锡]]矿<ref>{{cite web|title=Kuala Lumpur History|url=http://all.talkmalaysia.com/kuala-lumpur/kuala-lumpur-history/|publisher=All Malaysia|accessdate=2009-09-15|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091018073627/http://all.talkmalaysia.com/kuala-lumpur/kuala-lumpur-history/|archivedate=2009-10-18}}</ref>，矿场也由此成为贸易聚集之处。锡矿开采者们在吉隆坡登陆后便落脚于[[安邦|安邦]]，并在那里他们开设了第一座矿山<ref>{{cite book|title=The Story of Kuala Lumpur, 1857–1939|author= J.M. Gullick|publisher=Eastern Universities Press (M)|pages=8–9|year=1983|isbn=978-967-908-028-5}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://all.talkmalaysia.com/kuala-lumpur/kuala-lumpur-history/|title=Kuala Lumpur History|publisher=All Malaysia|access-date=2009-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091018073627/http://all.talkmalaysia.com/kuala-lumpur/kuala-lumpur-history/|archive-date=2009-10-18|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>Middlebrook & Gullick, ''op. cit.'', 1983: 18.</ref>。吉隆坡是[[巴生河|巴生河]]上游最远的地方，方便乘船运送补给品，因此成为锡矿的集散地。在锡矿开采的推动下，吉隆坡开始逐步发展并修建多条道路。{{sfn|Gullick|1955|page=10}}<ref>{{cite book|title=Kuala Lumpur: An Amalgam of Tin, Rubber, and Races : a Brief Review of the City's Historical, Physical, and Psychological Development : a Report|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=J9RLAQAAMAAJ|author=Willard Anderson Hanna|publisher=American Universities Field Staff|year=1959|access-date=2018-04-05|archive-date=2019-07-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721080811/https://books.google.com/books?id=J9RLAQAAMAAJ|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Kuala Lumpur: 100 Years|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sBZwAAAAMAAJ|year=1959|publisher=Kuala Lumpur Municipal Council|access-date=2018-04-05|archive-date=2019-07-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721080813/https://books.google.com/books?id=sBZwAAAAMAAJ|url-status=live}}</ref>

锡矿开采者合伙组成工人组织，包括客家族群为主的[[海山会|海山会]]和福建族群为主的[[义兴会|义兴会]]<ref name="kiat">{{cite web|url=http://kiat.net/malaysia/KL/history.html |title=From tin town to tower city |publisher=kiat.net |access-date=2010-09-28 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100727225206/http://kiat.net/malaysia/KL/history.html |archive-date=2010-07-27 }}</ref>。这两大华人工人组织经常为了锡矿利息产生争斗<ref name="Gullick2">{{cite journal|url=http://myrepositori.pnm.gov.my/bitstream/123456789/2265/1/JB1865_MBRA.pdf|title=Kuala Lumpur 1880–1895|author=J.M. Gullick|journal=Journal of the Malayan Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society|volume=24|issue=4|pages=12–14|year=1955|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528182107/http://myrepositori.pnm.gov.my/bitstream/123456789/2265/1/JB1865_MBRA.pdf|archive-date=2015-05-28|url-status=dead}}</ref>。由于斗争不断导致矿场时常停工，因而促使当时统治[[雪兰莪|雪兰莪]]的英国殖民政府和马来酋长委任一位「[[甲必丹|甲必丹]]」（意指华人领袖）管理吉隆坡的华人社区<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ow0pA3HchHQC&pg=PA49|title=The Consumption of Kuala Lumpur|author=Ziauddin Sardar|page=49|publisher=Reaktion Books|date=2000-08-01|isbn=978-1-86189-057-3|access-date=2017-09-02|archive-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804121030/https://books.google.com/books?id=Ow0pA3HchHQC&pg=PA49|url-status=live}}</ref>。吉隆坡早期的重要[[马来人|马来]]人物包括成为「拿督大港」（意指商人首领）的哈芝·莫哈末·塔希尔<ref name="gulllick 3"/>。[[苏门答腊|苏门答腊]]的[[米南佳保人|米南佳保人]]为吉隆坡[[贸易|贸易]]和建立烟草种植园的另一个重要群体，这个群体的著名人物包括拿督萨蒂、奥斯曼·阿都拉、莫哈末·努尔以及参与了甘榜峇鲁早期发展计划的哈芝·莫哈末·泰益。<ref>Nelmawarni Bungo, Nordin Hussin; Merantau ke Kuala Lumpur: Tradisi merantau dan berdagang masyarakat Minang, 2011</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/community/2014/06/13/life-is-colourful-on-infamous-road-named-after-a-wealthy-tradesman-jalan-haji-taib-is-more-known/|title=Life is colourful on infamous road|author1=Yip Yoke Teng|author2=Muhamad Shahril Rosli|work=The Star|date=2014-06-13|access-date=2014-06-13|archive-date=2015-12-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151219051324/http://www.thestar.com.my/news/community/2014/06/13/life-is-colourful-on-infamous-road-named-after-a-wealthy-tradesman-jalan-haji-taib-is-more-known/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.malaysiandigest.com/features/77922-malaysian-road-names-who-is-who.html|title=Malaysian Road Names: Who's Who?|publisher=Malaysian Digest|date=2013-06-18|access-date=2014-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630181136/http://www.malaysiandigest.com/features/77922-malaysian-road-names-who-is-who.html|archive-date=2017-06-30|url-status=dead}}</ref>

当时的吉隆坡是一个有着许多[[社会|社会]]和[[政治|政治]]问题的小镇。由于缺乏适当的[[卫生|卫生]]设施和[[地理|地理]]位置，当时的吉隆坡饱受疾病困扰和遭受[[洪水|洪水]]威胁。此外，吉隆坡早期的建筑物几乎都是用[[木头|木头]]和[[棕榈|棕榈]]叶茅草建造，因此也经常发生火灾。

=== 雪兰莪内战 ===
1867至1874年期间，吉隆坡因锡矿收入的问题卷入了{{tsl|en|Klang War|雪兰莪内战}}。当时的甲必丹[[叶亚来|叶亚来]]<ref name="Fatt2011"/>选择与{{tsl|ms|Tunku Dhiauddin ibn Sultan Zainal Rashid I|东姑古丁}}结盟，而敌对的华人帮派则与拉惹马哈迪结盟。由于{{tsl|ms|Raja Asal|拉惹阿萨}}和苏坦布阿沙转向支持拉惹马哈迪，吉隆坡随后在1872年被拉惹马哈迪占领并烧毁。叶亚来后来逃离吉隆坡在[[巴生|巴生]]组建了另一支战斗部队，并在来自彭亨战士的帮助下于1873年3月1日从拉惹马哈迪手中夺回吉隆坡的控制权<ref name="Gullick2"/>。

